<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="16" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Material examined.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="15" pageNumber="16">NHM_453 NHMUK 20170069.1-2, collected 2013-10-21, 13.90165 -116.59, 4163 m. http://data.nhm.ac.uk/object/ce9cbed0-82cc-420d-baad-fdfff7cc0986</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="17" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<pageBreakToken pageId="16" pageNumber="17" start="start">Description</pageBreakToken>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Subcircular to slightly oblique with slightly sinuous posterior margin. Periostracum with short, fine, bristles aligned in radial rows. Ligament small, triangular, set in shallow resilifer. Hinge teeth robust, 4 anterior and 5 posterior. Inner shell margin smooth. Voucher NHM_453 shell length 4.6 mm, height 4.3mm (Fig. 15).</paragraph>
